\[
\text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} \times \text{distance between centers} \times \text{difference of radii}
\]
Plugging in the values:
\[
\text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} \times 30 \times (24 - 6) = \frac{1}{2} \times 30 \times 18 = 15 \times 18 = 270
\]

Thus, the area of the triangular region bounded by the three common tangent lines of these two circles is \(\boxed{270}\).
